      <hedline>
        <hl1>Rheingold's Return</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Stephen R Dujack letter on March 31 article on return of Rheingold Extra Dry Lager Beer to New York area (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What joy in Sudsville to hear that Rheingold Extra Dry Lager Beer is returning to New York, and as a sponsor of the Mets, too (''Bringing Back a Taste of Brooklyn: Rheingold,'' news article, March 31)!</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>What joy in Sudsville to hear that Rheingold Extra Dry Lager Beer is returning to New York, and as a sponsor of the Mets, too (''Bringing Back a Taste of Brooklyn: Rheingold,'' news article, March 31)!</p>
        <p>But it won't be the same until they take down the Budweiser sign on the Shea Stadium scoreboard and replace it with Rheingold's famous blinking sign from the Mets' original ball park, the Polo Grounds.</p>
        <p>Talk about marketing savvy. When a fielding call was in doubt, all eyes rose to the Rheingold logo. Either the ''h'' would be winking  for a hit or the ''e'' for an error.</p>
        <p>STEPHEN R. DUJACK  Alexandria, Va., March 31, 1998</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
